 {"id":"rust_proxy-3q7","title":"Add SIGHUP handler for manual reload trigger","description":"## Scope

Add a SIGHUP signal handler that triggers config reload, following Unix conventions used by nginx, HAProxy, and other production services.

## Rationale

SIGHUP-triggered reload is the standard Unix pattern for daemon reconfiguration. Users familiar with other services will expect `kill -HUP <pid>` to reload config. This also enables integration with systemd's `systemctl reload` mechanism.

## Implementation Details

### Signal Handler Setup

```rust
use tokio::signal::unix::{signal, SignalKind};

async fn setup_sighup_handler(config_holder: Arc<ConfigHolder>) {
    let mut sighup = signal(SignalKind::hangup())
        .expect("Failed to register SIGHUP handler");

    tokio::spawn(async move {
        loop {
            sighup.recv().await;
            tracing::info!("Received SIGHUP, reloading configuration");

            match config_holder.reload().await {
                Ok(Some(diff)) => {
                    tracing::info!(
                        added = diff.proxies_added.len(),
                        removed = diff.proxies_removed.len(),
                        settings = diff.settings_changed.len(),
                        "Configuration reloaded"
                    );
                }
                Ok(None) => {
                    tracing::info!("Configuration unchanged");
                }
                Err(e) => {
                    tracing::error!(error = %e, "Failed to reload configuration");
                }
            }
        }
    });
}
```

### Platform Considerations

SIGHUP is Unix-only. On Windows, we'd need a different mechanism (named pipe, file trigger, etc.). For now, conditionally compile:

```rust
#[cfg(unix)]
async fn setup_signal_handlers(config_holder: Arc<ConfigHolder>) {
    setup_sighup_handler(config_holder).await;
}

#[cfg(not(unix))]
async fn setup_signal_handlers(_config_holder: Arc<ConfigHolder>) {
    // No-op on Windows for now
    tracing::debug!("SIGHUP handler not available on this platform");
}
```

### Integration with Daemon Startup

Call `setup_signal_handlers()` early in `run_daemon()`:

```rust
pub async fn run_daemon() -> Result<()> {
    let config_holder = Arc::new(ConfigHolder::new(config, config_path));

    setup_signal_handlers(config_holder.clone()).await;

    // ... rest of daemon startup
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- SIGHUP triggers config reload on Unix systems
- Handler logs success/failure clearly
- Graceful no-op on non-Unix platforms
- Multiple rapid SIGHUPs handled correctly (not queued up)","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-18T13:56:08.480076867-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-18T13:56:08.480076867-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rust_proxy-3q7","depends_on_id":"rust_proxy-7or","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-18T13:57:06.937533371-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"}]}
